ou won't just learn from books—you'll learn from life  An AHS education means more than just lectures and lab time. Our students are active in the community and in their fields, creating opportunities and forming relationships that shape their future. We believe that you’re always learning, no matter where you are.  From research to community engagement to student groups and events, whatever your interests are, you’ll find support to make your time here what you want it to be.      Our students in action            Transfer training at the Chinese American Service League  AHS student volunteers conduct training workshops for more than 300 home healthcare aides      See them in action              Learning around the globe  Make the world your campus, participate in our study abroad program      See them in action              Learning to innovate, collborate under pressure  The Health Tech Jam brought together AHS students and issued a challenge: develop a technological solution to a common health care problem — and do it in just six hours      See them in action            The AHS experience        Student organizations   Get involved in activities with students that share your interests         Events   From seminars to bake sales, there's always something to do on campus         Campus recreation   Providing recreational experiences which positively engage students through learning and leadership opportunities         UIC Diversity   Promoting an organizational culture and structure, grounded on the principles of access, equity and inclusion         UIC Office of Study Abroad   Supporting as many students as possible in becoming effective and influential leaders in civil society         UIC Student Life   Dedicated to providing a welcoming environment for its students and fostering a sense of belonging                     Inside AHS  The online community for and by students, faculty and staff  Inside AHS connects you with news, events and resources hand-picked and posted by other AHS’ers. If you want to get a glimpse inside our college, this is the place!   Go Inside AHS        AHS Magazine   AHS Magazine is the premier publication for and about members and friends of the UIC College of Applied Health Sciences community. Learn about all the great things happening in and beyond our classrooms.       Contact the editor       Browse the archive       Request a print copy             Read the winter 2020 issue              Read the summer 2019 issue             Read the winter 2019 issue                College of Applied Health Sciences    Back to main content           Applying    Expand Applying menu          Degrees and Deadlines    Beyond the Classroom    Tuition and Aid    Newly Admitted Students      Academics    Expand Academics menu          Departments and Programs      Research    Expand Research menu          Research Labs and Centers    Metabolic Kitchen      Community Services    Expand Community Services menu          Assistive Technology Unit    Developmental Disabilities Family Clinic    Occupational Therapy Faculty Practice    Physical Therapy Faculty Practice      Alumni    Expand Alumni menu          Give to AHS    Expand Give to AHS menu          Give to AHS    Where to Give      AHS Alumni Awards    Expand AHS Alumni Awards menu          Alumni Award Recipients      Meet Our Alumni    Corporate Partners Program    News    Events    Contact      About AHS    Expand About AHS menu          College News    College Calendar    Committees    Contact                  College of  Applied Health  Sciences       UI Health Logo                            Quick Links    Calendar    Directory    News    Inside AHS    Graduation      Resources    Academic Support and Achievement Program    Student Resources    Faculty and Staff Resources    Academic Calendar      Tools    myUIC    GoogleApps@UIC    Webmail    Blackboard    Nessie        Connect with AHS    Contact us    Apply Now    Give to AHS         1919 W Taylor St,